 properly the dynamics of conflict and balance, means and ends. Without that ability, even a superiority of dollars, numbers, and weaponry will not necessarily translate to victory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aConflict and Peace. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066278808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311070065740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048519415zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048519415423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048519415.jpg  a978-3-11-060651-5  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070065-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK